{{general relativity}}
In [[physics]], '''relativistic chaos''' is the application of [[chaos theory]] to [[dynamical system]]s described primarily by [[general relativity]], and also [[special relativity]].
One of the earlier references on the topic is (Barrow 1982) and a particularly relevant result is that relativistic chaos is coordinate invariant (Motter 2003).
