The '''Stacks Project''' is an [[open source]] collaborative mathematics textbook writing project with the aim to cover "[[algebraic stack]]s and the [[algebraic geometry]] needed to define them".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stacks.math.columbia.edu/about |title=Stacks Project — About |website=Stacks.math.columbia.edu |date= |accessdate=2016-11-26}}</ref>  {{As of|2018|03}}, the book consists of 109 chapters <ref>{{cite web|url=http://stacks.math.columbia.edu/browse |title=Stacks Project — Chapters |website=Stacks.math.columbia.edu |date= |accessdate=2016-11-26}}</ref> spreading over 6000 pages. The maintainer of the project, who reviews and accepts the changes, is [[Aise Johan de Jong]].<!-- TODO: the chapter list with links -->

