'''Time-domain harmonic scaling''' (TDHS) is a method for [[Audio timescale-pitch modification|time-scale modification]] of speech (or other audio signals),<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Richard V. Cox |author2=Ronald E. Crochiere |author3=James D. Johnston |date=February 1983 | title = Real-time implementation of time domain harmonic scaling of speech for rate modification and coding | journal = IEEE Transactions on Acoustics, Speech, and Signal Processing | volume = ASSP-31 | issue = 1 | pages = 258–272 | url = http://sipl.technion.ac.il/Info/new/Teaching/Experiments/EXP-Speech/0258cox.pdf | format = PDF }}</ref> allowing the apparent rate of speech articulation to be changed without affecting the pitch-contour and the time-evolution of the [[formant]] structure.<ref>{{ cite journal |author1=Moulines, Eric |author2=Jean Laroche. |lastauthoramp=yes | title = Non-parametric techniques for pitch-scale and time-scale modification of speech. | journal = Speech communication | volume = 16 | issue = 2 | year = 1995 | pages = 175–205 | url = http://sipl.technion.ac.il/new/Teaching/Projects/spring2007/TimeScale.pdf | format = PDF | doi=10.1016/0167-6393(94)00054-e }}</ref> TDHS differs from other time-scale modification algorithms in that time-scaling operations are performed in the [[time domain]] (not the [[frequency domain]]).<ref>{{ cite journal | author = Malah, D. A. V. I. D., R. Crochiere, and R. Cox. | title = Performance of transform and subband coding systems combined with harmonic scaling of speech | journal = IEEE Transactions on Acoustics, Speech, and Signal Processing | volume = 29 | issue = 2 | year = 1981 | pages = 273–283. | url = http://sipl.technion.ac.il/new/Teaching/Projects/spring2007/TimeScale.pdf | format = PDF | doi=10.1109/tassp.1981.1163547 }}</ref>
== History == Proposed by D. Malah in 1979<ref> {{cite journal | author = David Malah |date=April 1979 | title = Time-domain algorithms for harmonic bandwidth reduction and time scaling of speech signals | journal = IEEE Transactions on Acoustics, Speech, and Signal Processing | volume = ASSP-27 | issue = 2 | pages = 121–133 | url = http://sipl.technion.ac.il/Info/new/Teaching/Experiments/EXP-Speech/0121mala.pdf | format = PDF }}</ref>
